XML_CASESUMMARY.SUMMARY:
The crash occurred in the northbound lane of a two-lane undivided north/south roadway. The roadway was bituminous and level, with a posted speed limit of 80 kmph (50 mph). It was afternoon on a weekday. The road was dry. Traffic flow southbound was at a standstill as a result of road closures elsewhere in the county due to forest fire activity. The traffic heading north was light.
V1, a 2006 Pontiac Grand Prix with two occupants, was traveling south and the driver became frustrated with the traffic. The driver then attempted an illegal U-turn, pulling out in front of V2, a 2000 Jeep Wrangler with one occupant, which had been traveling north. V2 struck V1 in the right rear quarter panel, spinning V1 clockwise approximately 180 degrees. V1 mounted the curb before coming to rest. Neither vehicle took any avoidance maneuver.
V1 was driven by a 70-year-old male who reported no injuries. V1 was also occupied by a 66-year-old female that reported a complaint of pain and was transported. On-scene personnel reported that the driver of V1 was transporting his occupant to a doctor's appointment when he became frustrated with the southbound traffic and attempted an illegal U-turn. V1 crossed the double yellow centerline in front of V2, which was northbound. V2 struck V1 in the northbound lane. The driver of V1 refused an interview.
The Critical Pre-crash Event for V1 was "This vehicle traveling over the lane line on the left side of travel lane." The Critical Reason for the Critical Event was a driver related factor - illegal maneuver; the driver attempted an illegal U-turn. Associated factors coded to this driver include being in a hurry to transport his passenger to a doctor's appointment and the road congestion in the southbound direction.
V2 was driven by a 45-year-old female who reported no injuries. The driver stated that she was traveling northbound when V1 suddenly turned in front of her. She took no avoidance maneuver.
The Critical Pre-crash Event for V2 was "Other vehicle encroachment from opposite direction - over left lane line." No Critical Reason for the Critical Event was assigned to this vehicle. The only associated factor coded was the road congestion in the southbound direction.
